2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper presents a discrete version of the problem and uses linear programming formulation to solve it. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves game-theoretic concepts such as NP-completeness and hardness of problems. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper uses numerical methods to solve the problem of finding the least area surface. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an algorithmic approach to solve the problem and uses concepts from computational geometry and linear programming.
